rComments: His class was boring, he spoke mostly monotone and repeated the same thing over and over again for an hour. Taking notes wasnt necessary given there were no evaluations of what you learnt. Sitting through an hour and a half of his class was torture and felt like forever. It honestly felt like a waste of my time to be there.

Awesome prof, super interesting lectures and discussion topics, very funny, took us on a field trip. He's super knowledgeable and encourages students to delve into topics that interest them. He also took us out to Café Nostalgica at the end of the semester which was really fun.

Ahhhh Schryburt....I've had him for a lot of classes. He is witty, inspirational, sarcastic, and sooo well-informed on any subject that he teaches. A real theatre geek if you ever find one. I wish I could do my whole bachelor again for this prof. If you can take a class with him DO IT!!! (and he'll make you work for it)
Super Prof. Ses cours ne sont pas faciles, mais il explique clairement et est toujours prêt à aider dans le besoin. C'est un des meilleurs profs que j'ai eu lors de mon séjour à l'Université.
I've had him for all four years of univ. He is so well organised and quite clear. He's passionate about what he teaches and shares that passion with you (probably).
WOW!! The best teacher I ever had in my life. His classes are a lot of fun and he is really interesting. Recommend his classes to EVERYBODY!
